<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id4d32330e-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s20710"><num value="20710">§ 20710.</num><heading> Education and outreach to trafficking survivors</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Attorney General shall make available, on the website of the Office of Juvenile Justice and Delinquency Prevention, a database for trafficking victim advocates, crisis hotline personnel, foster parents, law enforcement personnel, and crime survivors that contains information on—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4d32330f-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s20710/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> counseling and hotline resources;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4d323310-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s20710/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> housing resources;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4d323311-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s20710/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> legal assistance; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id4d323312-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d" identifier="/us/usc/t34/s20710/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> other services for trafficking survivors.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id4d323313-5dcd-11f1-b11b-9e551e93f87d">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/164/tII/s210">Pub. L. 109–164, title II, § 210</ref>, formerly <ref href="/us/pl/114/22/tI/s119">Pub. L. 114–22, title I, § 119</ref>, <date date="2015-05-29">May 29, 2015</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/129/247">129 Stat. 247</ref>; renumbered <ref href="/us/pl/109/164/s210">§ 210 of Pub. L. 109–164</ref>, <ref href="/us/pl/117/347/tI/s106/b/1">Pub. L. 117–347, title I, § 106(b)(1)</ref>, <date date="2023-01-05">Jan. 5, 2023</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/6204">136 Stat. 6204</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
